        "body": "Default render hints: stroke `#7b61ff`, width `2`, dash `solid`, label tone `accent`, routing hint `curved`. Instance overrides may win when present.",
        "strength": "default",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "rule",
          "sourceRef": "/library/classes/nodes/skill-contract/rule.node-class.node",
          "ref": "/library/classes/nodes/skill-contract/rule.node-class.node"
        },
        "definitionKey": "rule",
        "markdown": "## Render defaults\n\nUse a clear blue curved path that reads as outbound navigation rather than local explanation."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "graph-entry-guardrail",
      "type": "guardrail",
      "label": "Guardrail",
      "position": {
        "x": 880,
        "y": 620
      },
      "width": 420,
      "height": 250,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "title": "When Not To Use It",
        "body": "Do not use `graph.implements` for dependency, sequence, or weak reference. If the source does not concretely realize the target, a plain edge or another class is the correct model.",
        "severity": "high",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "guardrail",
          "sourceRef": "/library/classes/nodes/skill-contract/guardrail.node-class.node",
          "ref": "/library/classes/nodes/skill-contract/guardrail.node-class.node"
        },
        "definitionKey": "guardrail",
        "markdown": "## Guardrail\n\nDo not use for local content inside the same graph. This class is for leaving the current graph context."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "graph-entry-failure-mode",
      "type": "failure-mode",
      "label": "Failure Mode",
      "position": {
        "x": 1360,
        "y": 620
      },
      "width": 420,
      "height": 250,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "title": "Common Failure Mode",
        "body": "The implementation relationship becomes misleading when authors draw it for loose inspiration or adjacency instead of concrete fulfillment. That makes traceability surfaces lie and weakens legend meaning.",
        "likelihood": "medium",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "failure-mode",
          "sourceRef": "/library/classes/nodes/skill-contract/failure-mode.node-class.node",
          "ref": "/library/classes/nodes/skill-contract/failure-mode.node-class.node"
        },
        "definitionKey": "failure-mode",
        "markdown": "## Failure mode\n\nIf used on local content, users may read internal content as if it were a separate graph destination."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "graph-entry-procedure",
      "type": "procedure",
      "label": "Procedure",
      "position": {
        "x": 400,
        "y": 620
      },
      "width": 420,
      "height": 260,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "title": "How To Apply It",
        "body": "1. Start with a plain edge between an implementation artifact and the thing it implements.\n2. If the source concretely realizes the target, assign `graph.implements`.\n3. Leave the base edge valid and let the class provide meaning and defaults.\n4. Override styling only when the local graph needs a special emphasis.",
        "steps": [
          "Create a base edge",
          "Assign the class only when implementation is concrete",
          "Let the class own meaning",
          "Override locally only when necessary"
        ],
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "procedure",
          "sourceRef": "/library/classes/nodes/skill-contract/procedure.node-class.node",
          "ref": "/library/classes/nodes/skill-contract/procedure.node-class.node"
        },
        "definitionKey": "procedure",
        "markdown": "## Procedure\n\nAttach this class to hub-to-port edges that open other graphs. Keep labels like `entry` or `section` as instance-level copy when useful."
      }
